## 7. 🧩 Implementation Details

### 7.1 Facts

Facts define the base relationships:

```prolog id="f1a2b3"
parent(tom, bob).
parent(tom, liz).
parent(bob, ann).
parent(bob, pat).
parent(pat, jim).
```

Gender facts:

```prolog id="f4c5d6"
male(tom).
male(bob).
male(pat).
male(jim).

female(liz).
female(ann).
```

---

### 7.2 Rules

#### Father

```prolog id="r1"
father(X, Y) :- parent(X, Y), male(X).
```

#### Mother

```prolog id="r2"
mother(X, Y) :- parent(X, Y), female(X).
```

#### Grandparent

```prolog id="r3"
grandparent(X, Y) :- parent(X, Z), parent(Z, Y).
```

#### Sibling

```prolog id="r4"
sibling(X, Y) :- parent(Z, X), parent(Z, Y), X \= Y.
```

#### Ancestor (Recursive Rule)

```prolog id="r5"
ancestor(X, Y) :- parent(X, Y).
ancestor(X, Y) :- parent(X, Z), ancestor(Z, Y).
```

#### Descendant

```prolog id="r6"
descendant(X, Y) :- ancestor(Y, X).
```

